## Landing Page Requirements

The landing page should present Alivia’s Apothecary as:

> “Reading, PA · small-batch aroid studio with live monitoring and curated care.”

Sections Cursor should assume exist / maintain:

### 1. Hero Section
- Editorial block on left: headline + paragraph
- Feature panel on right: logo/emblem, key offerings (timelapse, live feed, events, etc.)
- CTA buttons:
  - Explore care guides
  - View inventory / Shop plants
- Tone: high-end, calm, confident. No mysticism.

### 2. Studio Features Row
3–4 cards such as:
- Small-batch greenhouse (number of aroids in rotation)
- Care concierge (personalized care plans)
- 3D corm vessels / corm pots
- Monitoring & timelapse

Each card:
- Simple icon
- Short heading
- 1–2 line description

### 3. Greenhouse Window (Gallery + Live)
Use a `GreenhouseWindow` component to surface:

- Live feed status (live vs paused)
- Button: `View timelapse` / `Watch live`
- Snapshot strip / gallery preview

Props:

```ts
type GreenhouseWindowProps = {
  liveStreamEnabled: boolean;
  liveStreamUrl?: string | null;
  galleryImages: { src: string; alt: string }[];
};
Behavior:

If liveStreamEnabled && liveStreamUrl → embed iframe in a card.

Else → show “Camera feed paused” / next steps note.

Always render a gallery preview grid (3–4 recent frames).

